{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Brackenhurst Cricket Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Southwell, Nottinghamshire|Southwell]], [[Nottinghamshire]] | establishment = 1846 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1846 | club1 = Gentlemen of Southwell | date = 31 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/753.html Ground profile }}
'''Brackenhurst Cricket Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground near [[Southwell, Nottinghamshire|Southwell]], [[Nottinghamshire]] on the east side of the [[A612 road]].<ref>Cricket Grounds of Nottinghamshire P.Wynne-Thomas ACS 1984 p.15</ref> The first positive mention of the ground was on the [[Ordnance Survey]] map which appear after the 1830s survey. It was used by the Nottinghamshire Gentlemen as well as by local clubs. In 1846, the Gentlemen of Southwell with Five men given and A Mynn, played [[England national cricket team|England]] in what is the grounds only [[first-class cricket|first-class]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/753_f.html First-Class matches played on Brackenhurst Cricket Ground]</ref> The ground has held 6 [[Second XI Championship]] matches for the [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire Second XI]] between 1967 and 1995, the last of which saw the Nottinghamshire Second XI play the [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex Second XI]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/753_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Brackenhurst Cricket Ground]</ref>
The ground was bought by [[Nottinghamshire County Council]] in 1947<ref>Cricket Grounds of Nottinghamshire P.Wynne-Thomas ACS 1984 p.15</ref> and is today surrounded by [[Nottingham Trent University]] [[Nottingham_Trent_University#Campuses|Brackenhurst Campus]]. It is still in use to this day and is the home venue of [[Southwell Cricket Club]],<ref>[http://www.southwellcc.co.uk/index.html Southwell Cricket Club] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111202041642/http://www.southwellcc.co.uk/index.html |date=December 2, 2011 }}</ref> who until 2004 played in the [[Nottinghamshire Cricket Board Premier League]].
