{{Infobox Korean name |title=Korea National Training Center |img= |caption= |hangul=태릉선수촌 |hanja=泰陵選手村 |rr=Taereung seonsuchon |mr=T‘aerŭng sŏnsuchon }} '''Korea National Training Center''', also known as the '''Taereung Training Center''', located in [[Gongneung-dong]], [[Nowon-gu]], in the northeast part of [[Seoul]], is the only national athletic training center of [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.encyber.com/search_w/ctdetail.php?masterno=154518&contentno=154518 |script-title=ko:태릉선수촌 泰陵選手村 |publisher=[[Doosan Encyclopedia]] |accessdate=2008-05-15 |language=Korean }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Since its establishment on 30 June 1966 by the [[Korea Sports Council]] (대한체육회 大韓體育會), Taereung Training Center has been the home of Korean sports activities. It consists of 24 buildings, including training facilities, gymnasiums and dormitories in an area of {{convert|100000|m2|acre}}. The training facilities accommodate 20 different sport events such as athletics, [[gymnastics]], [[archery]], [[taekwondo]], [[wrestling]], [[swimming (sport)|swimming]], and others.<ref>[http://www.sports.or.kr/player_eng/KOC/KOC_ove.jsp Welcome to Korea National Training Center<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121219213839/http://www.sports.or.kr/player_eng/KOC/KOC_ove.jsp |date=2012-12-19 }}</ref>
