{{coord|51.256|-1.623|display=title}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground = Perriam Down cricket ground | image = | caption = | location = [[Ludgershall, Wiltshire]] | home club = [[Thomas Assheton Smith I|Assheton Smith's XI]] | county club = | established = 1787 | last used = 1796 }}
'''Perriam Down''' near [[Ludgershall, Wiltshire]] was used as a [[cricket]] venue for 6 [[first-class cricket|first-class]] and 3 other matches between 1787 and 1796.<ref name=FC>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121010153247/http://www.jl.sl.btinternet.co.uk/stampsite/cricket/histories/matches.html Classification of cricket matches from 1697 to 1825]</ref> It was a favoured venue of [[Thomas Assheton Smith I]] who patronised cricket in the area and organised all the matches.
